  "prompt": "Are Telugu speaking people offended by the slang Gultis?",
  "response": "The term \"Gultis\" is often used informally to refer to Telugu-speaking people, particularly in a light-hearted or humorous context. However, it can also be seen as derogatory or offensive to some. Reactions to the term can vary widely among individuals; some may embrace it or find it amusing, while others may take offense to it due to its connotation or context in which it is used.\n\nAs with many slang terms, the appropriateness of using \"Gultis\" largely depends on the relationship between the individuals in a conversation and the intent behind its use. It's always a good idea to be sensitive to how people prefer to identify and to avoid terms that could be hurtful or disrespectful.",
